<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-307-060  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 307 060.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  March 26 1990 v4 n12 p3(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FSG protests Navy PC LAN purchase. (Federal Systems Group Inc)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smithmidford, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Federal Systems Group Inc (FSG) is protesting the Navy's $400million PC LAN procurement, and has caused the procurement to besuspended.andP;  FSG charges that the RFP limits competition byrequiring support for OS-2 applications that are not commerciallyavailable; violates terms of the Navy's delegation of procurementauthority; is too vague to let vendors safely bid a fixed price;and ignores standard operating system requirements.andP;  The AirForce, which is in charge of procurement for the six-yearcontract, considers FSG's charges untimely and 'without merit'.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Federal Systems Group Inc. (contracts).andO;Topic:     Government ContractsRequest for ProposalsLocal Area NetworksAir ForceNavyLegal Issues.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>